              </ul>
            </form>
          </div>

          <h3 class="gray">Next Group Ride:</h3>

          <ul class="orgs ribbon">
            <%= render :partial => 'common/event_list' %>

          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="attribution">
          <p>Photo Attribution: <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/2.0/" class="white">Some rights reserved</a> by <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/everywhereatonce/" class="white">everywhereATonce</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  <article id="info" class="bg-red container second">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="twelvecol">
        <h1 class="white">Spoke Geek Cycling Club</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="sevencol">
        <div class="hero-image">&nbsp;</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fivecol last">
        <h2 class="white">Fun is the Golden Rule</h2>
        <p><strong>Spoke Geek</strong> is a casual bike club. Some of us are weekend warriors in spandex, others are commuters in jeans. We just like to get together to burn calories, drink beer, talk semicolons, increase our heart rates, bitch about our catered lunches (not enough bacon, too much bacon, GLUTEN), and work on our farmer&rsquo;s tans.</p>
        <p>We are an all-volunteer, not-for-profit organization. All proceeds from sponsorships, merch, etc go to:</p>
        <ul class="orgs">
          <li class="bullet"><strong>SF Bicycle Coalition</strong> to help them continue to advocate for our rights as cycists.</li>
          <li class="bullet"><strong>Electronic Frontier Foundation</strong> to help them continue to advocate for our rights as technologists.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For information, sponsorships, partnerships, press, and questions please email <a href="mailto:spokes@luckynerds.com" class="yellow">spokes@luckynerds.com</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>
